), and focused algebraic_laws test budget_priority_is_min passes (1/1). No additional edits needed in grpc/pipeline blocker files by completion time; branch state had advanced and blockers cleared.","created_at":"2026-02-25T19:51:24Z"},{"id":2015,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Peer-review slice (CopperHeron, 2026-02-26): identified API regression in src/grpc/client.rs where ResponseStream<T> implemented Streaming only for T: Unpin, unnecessarily rejecting valid !Unpin message types. Patched impl bound to T: Send and added regression test grpc::client::tests::response_stream_supports_non_unpin_messages using PhantomPinned payload to prove non-Unpin stream polling/drain works. Validation (all via rch): cargo check -p asupersync --lib PASS (remote exit=0); cargo test -p asupersync --lib response_stream_supports_non_unpin_messages -- --nocapture PASS (1/1); env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-copperheron-grpc-client cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings PASS (remote command exit=0; artifact retrieval emitted rsync vanished-file warnings after completion). Note: cargo fmt --check currently fails on unrelated pre-existing formatting drift in tests/race_bug_test.rs import order outside this slice.","created_at":"2026-02-26T00:01:17Z"},{"id":2016,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Follow-up: hardened validate_rpc_path in src/grpc/client.rs to reject empty/extra segments; added validate_rpc_path_rejects_empty_or_extra_segments test; rch check/test/clippy (lib) all PASS.","created_at":"2026-02-26T03:09:46Z"},{"id":2030,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"SunnyHollow: Build/clippy stabilization pass complete. Fixed clippy missing_docs in asupersync-macros/tests/compile_fail_tests.rs by adding crate-level docs. Validation via rch: cargo clippy -p asupersync-macros --test compile_fail_tests -- -D warnings (remote exit=0) and cargo build --workspace --lib --tests --bins (remote exit=0). Full cargo build --workspace --all-targets encountered worker storage exhaustion (No space left on device) when benches included; appears infra-related rather than source-level compile failure.","created_at":"2026-02-26T05:20:01Z"},{"id":2174,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"BrownCove","text":"BrownCove takeover slice (2026-03-02): auditing current modified surfaces. Found compile regression in tests/nextjs_bootstrap_harness.rs from new churn scenario (NextjsIntegrationSnapshot type/field mismatch). Repro (rch): cargo test --test nextjs_bootstrap_harness rapid_navigation_churn_with_interleaved_recovery_remains_deterministic -- --nocapture (exit 101). Applying minimal deterministic fix and re-running targeted rch tests.","created_at":"2026-03-02T06:58:38Z"},{"id":2175,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"BrownCove","text":"BrownCove review slice (2026-03-02): rch-offloaded audit found regression in new Next.js churn test on this branch state. Initial failure: compile mismatch from stale type assumptions (NextjsIntegrationSnapshot fields), then semantic mismatch in cancellation accounting. Applied narrow fix in tests/nextjs_bootstrap_harness.rs: set churn expectation to cancellation_count == 5 because hard-navigation scope invalidations increment cancellation_count alongside explicit CancelBootstrap events. Validation (all via rch): 1) cargo test --test nextjs_bootstrap_harness rapid_navigation_churn_with_interleaved_recovery_remains_deterministic -- --nocapture PASS after fix; 2) cargo test --test react_wasm_strictmode_harness rapid_restart_churn_keeps_event_sequence_balanced -- --nocapture PASS; 3) cargo test --lib symbolic_obligation -- --nocapture PASS (18/18 symbolic_obligation tests). Additional gates via rch: cargo check --all-targets PASS, cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings PASS, cargo fmt --check PASS.","created_at":"2026-03-02T07:12:14Z"},{"id":2290,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"DustyHarbor","text":"2026-03-04 DustyHarbor peer-review slice (web/extract compile frontier):\n\n1) Claimed + reserved focused surface:\n- src/web/extract.rs\n- src/web/router.rs\n- tests/net_http_ws_invariants.rs\n\n2) Findings/patch:\n- The prior all-target failure signature (E0308 around header_value_ci callsites) did not reproduce on fresh current-head compile.\n- Added deterministic regression coverage in src/web/extract.rs for case-insensitive Content-Type header-name handling:\n  - json_content_type_header_name_case_insensitive\n  - form_content_type_header_name_case_insensitive\n\n3) rch validation evidence:\n- Build 29739154870895039: env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-dusty-302-alltargets cargo check --all-targets => exit=0\n  (artifact sync emitted rsync vanished-file warnings post-compile; compile phase clean).\n- Build 29739154870895058: env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-dusty-302-alltargets cargo test -p asupersync --lib content_type_header_name_case_insensitive -- --nocapture => exit=0\n\n4) Cleanup notes:\n- Redundant follow-up probe builds were canceled after canonical passing evidence was captured (130 exits expected from cancellation).\n- Focused lib clippy run launched as additional gate evidence; if it remains infra-stale, this slice already has compile+test pass evidence for changed surface and no observed behavioral regression.","created_at":"2026-03-04T19:46:34Z"},{"id":2291,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"DustyHarbor","text":"Follow-up evidence capture:\n- Streaming output for build 29739154870895058 confirmed test execution details:\n  running 2 tests\n  web::extract::tests::form_content_type_header_name_case_insensitive ... ok\n  web::extract::tests::json_content_type_header_name_case_insensitive ... ok\n  test result: ok. 2 passed; 0 failed.\n\n- Focused clippy gate command () reached remote-exec completion with exit=0 in stream logs before sync-down cleanup; I canceled lingering post-exec artifact-sync tail to reduce shared queue pressure.","created_at":"2026-03-04T19:47:38Z"},{"id":2301,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"CoralBrook","text":"2026-03-04 CoralBrook takeover slice: auditing non-overlapping compile-risk surfaces in src/http/h1/http_client.rs (+ related HTTP client tests). Will run rch-offloaded check/clippy/tests and post deterministic evidence + any patches.","created_at":"2026-03-04T22:35:45Z"},{"id":2312,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"CoralBrook","text":"2026-03-04 CoralBrook review slice (HTTP/1 client upgrade path): found correctness bug where request_streaming dropped prefetched bytes when response body kind was Empty, which loses upgraded-protocol bytes on 101 Switching Protocols. Patched src/http/h1/client.rs to preserve read-ahead buffer for all body kinds; added ClientIncomingBody::into_inner_with_buffer() for callers needing transport + prefetched bytes; kept into_inner() as buffer-dropping convenience. Added deterministic regression test request_streaming_upgrade_preserves_prefetched_bytes. Validation: rch cargo test -p asupersync --lib request_streaming_upgrade_preserves_prefetched_bytes -- --nocapture PASS; rch env CARGO_INCREMENTAL=0 CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-coral-check4 cargo check --all-targets PASS; cargo fmt --check PASS. rch clippy all-targets currently fails on pre-existing unrelated lint in src/messaging/kafka_consumer.rs (significant_drop_tightening), outside this slice.","created_at":"2026-03-04T23:05:49Z"},{"id":2256,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"VioletForge","text":"Review slice (2026-03-04): audited active web extraction/router deltas and identified deterministic correctness defect in src/web/extract.rs. Path<T>/Query<T> scalar fast path now deserializes from values().next() without len()==1 guard, so multi-key maps can parse arbitrary first value (HashMap iteration order), producing nondeterministic and incorrect success for scalar targets (e.g., Query<u32> on ?a=1&b=2). Attempted exclusive reservation for src/web/extract.rs + src/web/router.rs but conflicted with active holder CopperDesert. Sent high-priority Agent Mail in thread br-28c51.302 with patch guidance: reintroduce len()==1 scalar guard and add regression tests that multi-parameter scalar extraction returns 400. No local patch applied in this slice due reservation ownership boundary; defect escalation recorded.","created_at":"2026-03-04T03:16:43Z"},{"id":2316,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"CoralBrook","text":"2026-03-05 CoralBrook follow-up HTTP hardening slice: added explicit guard against silent unread-prefetch drops in Http1Client::request_with_io. Changes: (1) new HttpError variant PrefetchedDataRemaining(usize) in src/http/h1/codec.rs; (2) request_with_io now uses into_inner_with_buffer() and returns PrefetchedDataRemaining when unread bytes remain; (3) regression test request_with_io_rejects_unread_prefetched_bytes in src/http/h1/client.rs (101 + prefetched bytes). Validation: rch cargo test -p asupersync --lib prefetched_bytes -- --nocapture PASS (includes request_streaming_upgrade_preserves_prefetched_bytes + new request_with_io_rejects_unread_prefetched_bytes); rch cargo check --all-targets compile phase PASS (exit=0 in stream logs) but artifact sync-down stalled in current rch window; rustfmt +nightly --edition 2024 --check on touched files PASS; rch clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings currently fails on unrelated pre-existing lint in src/util/arena.rs (manual_assert).","created_at":"2026-03-05T00:27:49Z"}]}
